From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: wow64: route AMD64-native (spoofed) to libwow64fex.dll instead of wow64cpu.dll

Companion to patch 0010 (which spoofs AMD64 as the user-visible native
machine via SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures replies). The wow64.dll
itself reads `native_machine` via `RtlWow64GetProcessMachines`, so after
patch 0010 lands, wow64.dll sees `native_machine = AMD64` even though we're
physically on ARM64.

The existing code (`dlls/wow64/syscall.c:750`) routes I386 wow64 boot to
`libwow64fex.dll` ONLY when `native_machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64`,
falling back to `wow64cpu.dll` otherwise. With the spoof active,
native_machine is AMD64 and the boot path lands on `wow64cpu.dll`, which
we don't build for aarch64 (it's in `aarch64_DISABLED_SUBDIRS` in the
Makefile). The 32-bit wine startup then dies with STATUS_DLL_NOT_FOUND at
wow64 init — observed with IK TONEX 1.12 (Inno Setup 6.4.2, 32-bit
installer wrapper).

Add the AMD64 branch so both the real native (ARM64) and the spoofed
native (AMD64) route to libwow64fex.dll. ARM64 stays as the primary because
that's still the actual host CPU; AMD64 is the user-facing lie.

diff --git a/dlls/wow64/syscall.c b/dlls/wow64/syscall.c
--- a/dlls/wow64/syscall.c
+++ b/dlls/wow64/syscall.c
@@ -747,8 +747,16 @@
         RtlInitUnicodeString( &nameW, L"\\Registry\\Machine\\Software\\Microsoft\\Wow64\\x86" );
         /* Default the ARM64 host's x86-emulation DLL to FEX-Emu's
          * libwow64fex.dll instead of Microsoft's xtajit.dll (which we
-         * don't ship). Matches patch 003 for the ARM64EC / x86_64 case. */
-        ret = (native_machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64 ? L"libwow64fex.dll" : L"wow64cpu.dll");
+         * don't ship). Matches patch 003 for the ARM64EC / x86_64 case.
+         *
+         * Accept BOTH ARM64 (real native) and AMD64 (spoofed native via
+         * patch 0010) — both map to the same FEX DLL on our build.
+         * Without the AMD64 branch, the post-spoof path lands on
+         * wow64cpu.dll which we don't ship for aarch64 and the 32-bit
+         * process dies with STATUS_DLL_NOT_FOUND at wow64 init. */
+        ret = (native_machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64 ||
+               native_machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64
+               ? L"libwow64fex.dll" : L"wow64cpu.dll");
         break;
     case IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARMNT:
         RtlInitUnicodeString( &nameW, L"\\Registry\\Machine\\Software\\Microsoft\\Wow64\\arm" );
